()\n    {\n        ASN1EncodableVector v = new ASN1EncodableVector();\n\n        v.add(version);\n        v.add(new DEROctetString(publicKey));\n\n        return new DERSequence(v);\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1779487485088}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering Java Constructor Testing**\n\nI’m thinking about a package-private inner class in a test, which might not be necessary as a top-level class. I wonder about Checkstyle rules regarding brace placement in Java. Using type annotations in variables seems fine, and I’m questioning dynamic coverage in this context. There might be concerns about public access for methods. Should I consider making an inner public constructor? Using the KeySpec class as inner seems complex, and there’s a chance user-code-filter issues could affect generated metadata from DESKeySpec.\n\n**Evaluating GraalVM Native Plugin Testing**\n\nI’m looking into the GraalVM Native plugin, specifically how `nativeTest` depends on the `test` configuration, especially regarding agent setup. In this repository, `nativeTest` might run JVM tests with an agent that excludes DESKeySpec due to the user-code-filter. This could lead to failures in generating the native image. Using a SecretKeySpec could help avoid reflection metadata issues, but I'm unsure if javax.crypto types are registered in the native image. I’m considering adding a test helper class from org.bouncycastle while being mindful of the user-code-filter rules.\n\n**Clarifying Testing Guidelines**\n\nI need to create or update tests solely under the test source root without making edits elsewhere. The task specifies not to generate or modify reachability metadata or Native Image configuration in the `src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image` directory. While using the user-code-filter seems acceptable, it’s better to adhere strictly to these rules. I could consider using an actual BC class instead of KeySpec with byte arrays, but I must be cautious of cast failures and native reflection metadata issues since it's from org.bouncycastle.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_06fa3b6f0dfd484f016a10d2ed9c448197bb063395b63577be\",\"type\